{
  "doc_id": "4820",
  "text": "Let M be a semi-finite von Neumann algebra and let τ be a faithful normal semi-finite trace on M. Denote by m τ the definition ideal of τ , i.e the set of all elements a ∈ M such that τ (|a|) < ∞. Then m τ is a * -algebra and, moreover m τ is a two sided ideal of M (see [CITATION_1] , Definition 2.17).",
